Notes on compilation 
====================
1) How to load shared library (.so) in Gradle-based project
+ Put the the shared library to every sub-folder of ./lib folder 
+ zip the ./lib folder and change the file extension to .jar 
+ Copy this newly created .jar file to ./app/libs folder 
+ Note that there is string line as "compile fileTree(dir: 'libs', include: ['*.jar'])" in build.gradle 


